1)Basic anatomy<br>
2)The Wooden Mannikan how to use it.<br>
3)Drawing figures to perspective(very well done, IMHO)<br>
4)Use of halftones and shadow while penciling.<br>
5)Many, many, MANY excellent pencil drawings of both men and women nude. <br>
6)Great text as well, not a whole lot but what he writes is both informative, practical(even by today's standards), and highly motivational.<br>
7)Endless tips and little snippets of how to's. <br>
<br>
I ran into this book at a tut site with a link to a site that has the complete book online(very small page sizes I d/led the entire site on a 56k and it took less than 30 minutes).<br>
The link is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.yoyodyne.net/loomis">www.yoyodyne.net/loomis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
I HIGHLY recommend you check this book out. This book should be in the PK library, it is far more flexible and far easier to learn by than any of the Burne Hogarth material(I have those and trust me no comparison as to which helped more). Go look at the introduction to the Loomis book. Its one you definately want to read and not just for the pictures. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
